Package tradestock.view.textfieldview

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    WithTextField
    This interface represents Views that with text field in them.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddStock
    This class represents the AddStock view when user do add stock operation, it enables user to add a stock to portfolio.
    BuyStockMoney
    The class represents the view when user do buy stock by a given amount of money operation.
    BuyStockView
    This class represents a view that user will see when user buy stocks.
    CheckCostByDateView
    This class represents a view when do check cost basis by date operation.
    CheckCostView
    This class represents a view when do check cost basis operation.
    CheckValueByDateView
    This class represents a view when do check total value by date operation.
    CheckValueView
    This class represents a view, when users do check value operation.
    CreatePortfolio
    This class represents the view when users do create portfolio operation.
    CreateStrategyInputStrategyBasic
    This class represent the view when user choose to create a strategy with an end date , it enables user type the basis information about the strategy, include the number of stocks in the strategy, the strategy name, start date, end date, interval, and how much money the user invest every period.
    DiffPercentageEndBasic
    This class represents the view when user choose to create a strategy with an end date and use different weight on every stock in a strategy.
    DiffPercentageNoEndBasic
    This class represents the view when user choose to create a strategy without an end date and use different weight on every stock in a strategy.
    EqualPercentageNoEndBasic
    This class represents the view when user choose to create a strategy without an end date and use same weight on every stock in a strategy.
    GetPortfolioDetailByDateView
    This class represents the view when users do examine a portfolio at a given date.
    GetPortfolioDetailView
    The class represents the view when users do examine portfolio operation.
    SetCommissionFee
    The class represents the view when user set commission fee.
    UseDiffPercentageEnd
    This class represents the view when user create a strategy with end date and choose use different weight on every stock, it enables user to type the stock symbols and its percentage.
    UseDiffPercentageNoEnd
    This class represents the view when user create a strategy without end date and choose use different weight on every stock, it enables user to type the stock symbols and its percentage.
    UseEqualPercentageEnd
    This class represents the view when user create a strategy with end date and choose use same weight on every stock, it enables user to type the stock symbols.
    UseEqualsPercentage
    This class represents the view when user create a strategy without end date and choose use same weight on every stock, it enables user to type the stock symbols.
